# Flipkart Gridlock Hackathon (Theme 2): AI Command Center Blueprint
**Author**: Senior Machine Learning Architect & Hackathon Mentor

This master blueprint details the complete system design, folder layouts, mathematical formulations, and engineering strategies for the **AI Command Center for Bengaluru Traffic Police**. This design is modeled directly after the working code modules in your repository.

---

## 1. System Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Ingestion & Storage Layer"
        CSV["Astram Incident Logs (CSV)"] -->|Data Imputation| SQL[("SQLite Database (traffic_ops.db)")]
        FEED["Officer Web Terminal"] -->|Post-Event Feedback| SQL
    end

    subgraph "Core ML & Graph Routing Engine"
        SQL -->|Dataset Loader| PREP["Preprocessor (StandardScaler + OneHotEncoder)"]
        PREP -->|Feature Matrices| XGB["XGBClassifier (XGBoost Pipeline)"]
        XGB -->|1. Predict Congestion Severity| RULE["Resource Rule Engine (optimization_engine.py)"]
        
        GRAPH["NetworkX Directed Graph (route_recommender.py)"] -->|2. Find Alternate Routes| ALGO["A* Search (Haversine Heuristic)"]
    end

    subgraph "Operational Output & Interfaces"
        RULE -->|Police & Barricades Dispatch| UI["Streamlit Command Dashboard (app.py)"]
        ALGO -->|Recommended Diversions| UI
        SQL -->|Density Coordinates| HEAT["Folium Heatmap Layer (map_dashboard.py)"]
        HEAT --> UI
    end

    subgraph "Closed-Loop Feedback"
        UI -->|Manual Form Input| FEED
        FEED -->|Accuracies & Drift Metrics| RETRAIN["Automatic Retrain Pipeline"]
        RETRAIN -->|Overwrite Serialized Weights| XGB
    end
```

